{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Hierarchies","text":"Hierarchies"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Four hierarchies are proposed for all layouts:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Default buttons are used for actions which are not mandatory or essential for the user."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"strong"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": The Strong “call for action” on the page should be singular and prominent, limited to one per view.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It should be reserved for the most critical action, such as “Next,” “Save,” “Submit,” etc."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"minimal"}]},{"text":": Minimal buttons are commonly used for actions that are considered less crucial. They can be used independently or together with a strong button.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"negative"}]},{"text":": Negative buttons should be used sparingly to warn of a destructive action,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for example, delete or remove, typically resulting in the opening of a confirmation dialog."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"code":"OUDSButton.Hierarchy.Negative","type":"codeVoice"},{"typ